"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1133212","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-06-25","<p>The number of women and men admitted to prison for ‘Non-Payment: Community charge / Council Tax’ can be viewed in Table A2.12 at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/796916/receptions-2018.ods" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/796916/receptions-2018.ods</a></p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2019-06-25T13:47:21.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1133212/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1133212/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1133212/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-06-19","Council Tax: Non-payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of people who received a custodial sentence for council tax debt were women in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","266691"
